The paper discusses the use of social technologies to propagate disinformation and manipulate the behavior of energy consumers, which is a security concern. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves modeling the propagation of disinformation through social networks, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SOC) and social influence (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the vulnerabilities of critical infrastructure, which is related to cyber-physical systems (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper involves conducting surveys to assess human behavior, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
